body:
@xiao1228 the repo has been updated recently to align more closely with darknet. Darknet trains for about 500,000 batches, or 270 epochs at batch size 16. There is an LR scheduler with a gamma of 0.1 built into darknet that acts around batch 450,000. The current repo is meant to replicate this more closely. So technically to get the best map you will want to train for 270 epochs roughly.

The loss function is still a bit of a question mark for me though, as when I apply the darknet loss strictly I do not get as good results (in the first 70 epochs) as with the current loss function.

Additionally, the plotted mAP does not align correctly to the COCO official map using pycocotools. We have a TODO to try to fix this.
